---
import LegalLayout from '../layouts/LegalLayout.astro';
import Prose from '../components/Prose.astro';
import { site } from '../data/site';
---
<LegalLayout
  title="Refund Policy"
  description="How Pinkflow handles refunds and billing issues."
  lastUpdated={site.lastUpdated.refunds}
>
  <Prose>
    <p>This Policy was last updated on {site.lastUpdated.refunds}.</p>

    <h2>1. Generally final once delivered or used</h2>
    <p>
      Namescape search packs are <strong>digital consumables</strong>. A pack is consumed
      when a search is run. Because we cannot reliably verify partial use, purchases are
      <strong>generally final once delivered or used</strong>, except where required by law
      or where there is a billing or delivery issue we can fix (see Section 4).
    </p>

    <h2>2. Why</h2>
    <p>
      Once you run a search, the value of the pack has been delivered. We have no way to
      "un-deliver" the suggestions, availability clues, or price guidance you received. This
      is the standard model for digital consumable products.
    </p>

    <h2>3. Statutory rights preserved</h2>
    <p>
      Nothing in this Policy waives any non-waivable consumer rights you may have under
      {site.jurisdiction} law, EU/UK consumer protection, or the law of your country of residence.
      If a local right entitles you to a refund in your specific circumstances, that right
      always applies.
    </p>

    <h2>4. Issues we will always fix</h2>
    <p>Contact us and we will make it right if any of these happen:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>You were <strong>charged twice</strong> for the same purchase due to a technical failure.</li>
      <li>You were charged but <strong>searches were not added</strong> to your account.</li>
      <li>An <strong>unauthorized transaction</strong> appears on your account &mdash; report it immediately.</li>
      <li>The service was <strong>materially unavailable</strong> at the time of purchase and you received no value.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>5. Timing</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>We respond to billing reports within <strong>{site.responseWindow}</strong>.</li>
      <li>We aim to resolve billing and delivery issues within <strong>{site.resolutionWindow}</strong> of your first report.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>6. How to report</h2>
    <p>
      Email <a href={`mailto:${site.email}`}>{site.email}</a> with your account email and the
      transaction ID if you have it. Please report billing issues within <strong>60 days</strong>
      of the transaction so we can investigate promptly.
    </p>

    <h2>7. About Paddle</h2>
    <p>
      Payment is processed by Paddle, the {site.paddle.role.toLowerCase()}. Your card statement
      will show <strong>{site.paddle.statementLabel}</strong>. For billing disputes, contact us
      first &mdash; we will resolve what we can directly and loop in Paddle when needed.
    </p>
  </Prose>
</LegalLayout>
